Added Data Science with Python

I created a list for resources for data science with Python. It includes not only libraries, but also links to tutorials, code snippets, blog posts and talks. The existing awesome list focues on papers, my list focuses on mainly on packages and is quite different. Think it would be a good addition to this repo.

Merge pull request #377 from ehmicky/patch-1

Add Cross-platform Node.js

Add Cross-platform Node.js

https://github.com/bcoe/awesome-cross-platform-nodejs

Libraries and resources related to writing Node.js that works on Windows, Mac, Linux and BSD, by @bcoe.

Why this matters: according to the [2018 Node.js user survey](https://nodejs.org/en/user-survey-report/#Primary-OS-Distro), 24% of Node.js developers use Windows locally and 41% use Mac. In production 85% use Linux and 1% use BSD.

Add awesome graph embedding repository.

The repository is an exhaustive list of graph representation learning research papers with reference implementations. The machine learning task is to create representations of whole graphs from a database e.g. molecules, financial transaction graphs etc. It covers factorization models, graph kernels, statistical fingerprints and deep learning.
